              <fr:day>7</fr:day>
            </fr:date>
            <fr:addr>jms-016L</fr:addr>
            <fr:route>http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-016L.xml</fr:route>
            <fr:title text="Monoid structure of strings">Monoid structure of <fr:link href="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-016I.xml" title="String over an alphabet" addr="jms-016I" type="local">strings</fr:link></fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Observation</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <html:p>By <fr:link href="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-016K.xml" title="Properties of concatenation" addr="jms-016K" type="local">Lemma <fr:contextual-number addr="jms-016K" /></fr:link>, <fr:link href="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-016I.xml" title="String over an alphabet" addr="jms-016I" type="local">strings</fr:link> under <fr:link href="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-016J.xml" title="Concatenation of strings" addr="jms-016J" type="local">concatenation</fr:link> form a <html:em>monoid</html:em>, but not a commutative monoid (indeed, we don’t have <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[uv=vu]]></fr:tex> unless either <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[u]]></fr:tex> or <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[v]]></fr:tex> is empty or <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[u=v]]></fr:tex>). Viewing <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\Sigma ^\star ]]></fr:tex> as a monoid, we see that the length function <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathopen {}\left \lvert -\right \rvert \mathclose {}}\colon  \Sigma ^\star \to \mathbb {N}]]></fr:tex> is a homomorphism of monoids from <fr:link href="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-016J.xml" title="Concatenation of strings" addr="jms-016J" type="local">strings</fr:link> to the additive monoid of the natural numbers:</html:p>
            <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[
 \begin {aligned}
 {\mathopen {}\left \lvert \epsilon \right \rvert \mathclose {}} &= 0\\
 {\mathopen {}\left \lvert uv\right \rvert \mathclose {}} &= {\mathopen {}\left \lvert u\right \rvert \mathclose {}}+{\mathopen {}\left \lvert v\right \rvert \mathclose {}}
 \end {aligned}
]]></fr:tex>
          </fr:mainmatter>
        </fr:tree>
        <fr:tree show-metadata="true" expanded="false" toc="false" numbered="false">
          <fr:frontmatter>
            <fr:authors>
              <fr:author>
                <fr:link href="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link>
              </fr:author>
            </fr:authors>
            <fr:date>
              <fr:year>2025</fr:year>
              <fr:month>2</fr:month>
              <fr:day>7</fr:day>
            </fr:date>
            <fr:addr>jms-016K</fr:addr>
            <fr:route>http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-016K.xml</fr:route>
            <fr:title text="Properties of concatenation">Properties of <fr:link href="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-016J.xml" title="Concatenation of strings" addr="jms-016J" type="local">concatenation</fr:link></fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Lemma</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <html:p><fr:link href="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-016J.xml" title="Concatenation of strings" addr="jms-016J" type="local">Concatenation</fr:link> satisfies several algebraic laws:</html:p>
            <html:ol><html:li>The <fr:link href="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-016J.xml" title="Concatenation of strings" addr="jms-016J" type="local">empty string</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\epsilon ]]></fr:tex> is a neutral element for <fr:link href="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-016J.xml" title="Concatenation of strings" addr="jms-016J" type="local">concatenation</fr:link> on both the left and right right:
   <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[\forall  u\in \Sigma ^\star \mathpunct {.} \epsilon  u = u\land  u\epsilon  = u]]></fr:tex></html:li>
 <html:li><fr:link href="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-016J.xml" title="Concatenation of strings" addr="jms-016J" type="local">Concatenation</fr:link> is associative:
  <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[
   \forall  u,v,w\in \Sigma ^\star 
   \mathpunct {.}
   u(vw) = (uv)w
  ]]></fr:tex></html:li></html:ol>
          </fr:mainmatter>
        </fr:tree>
      </fr:mainmatter>
    </fr:tree>
